  "body": "- [yes, asked, no one replied] I've asked for help in the [Truffle Gitter](http://gitter.im/Consensys/truffle) before filing this issue.\r\n\r\n---------------------------\r\n\r\n## Issue\r\n\r\neth_signTypedData doesn't work with hdwallet-provider\r\n\r\n## Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n```\r\nweb3.currentProvider.sendAsync({\r\n            jsonrpc: \"2.0\",\r\n            method: \"eth_signTypedData\",\r\n            params: [customerAddress, data],\r\n            //from: customerAddress,\r\n            id: new Date().getTime()\r\n        }, (err, result) => {\r\n...\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Expected Behavior\r\n\r\nTyped data successfully signed by ganache.\r\n\r\n## Actual Results\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/cgewecke/provider-engine/blob/master/subproviders/hooked-wallet.js doesn't support the correct eth_signTypedData spec, and the method fails.\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n* Operating System: Ubuntu\r\n* Ethereum client: Ganache CLI v6.2.5 (ganache-core: 2.3.3)\r\n* Truffle v5.0.2 (core: 5.0.2)\r\n* Node v10.15.0\r\n* npm version : 6.4.1\r\n\r\n## possible workaround\r\n\r\nInside hdwallet provide code:\r\n\r\n```\r\n  // hack1: make signTypedData work\r\n  {\r\n    let origHandler = hookedSubprovider.handleRequest.bind(hookedSubprovider);\r\n    hookedSubprovider.handleRequest = function(payload, next, end) {\r\n      switch(payload.method) {\r\n        case 'eth_signTypedData':\r\n          next();\r\n          break;\r\n        default:\r\n          return origHandler(payload, next, end)\r\n      }\r\n    }\r\n  }\r\nthis.engine.addProvider(hookedSubprovider);\r\n```\r\n\r\nAlthough I think to fix in hooked subprovider is better.",
